 rate regulation in the auto insurance industry, and provide broad overviews of the structure and economics of the insurance industry as a whole. Also addressed are the system of regulating insurance companies in the United States, who insures the insurers, and the effects of tax law changes in the 1980s on the prices of insurance policies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBusiness. 0aCasualty insurance. 0aProperty insurance. 0aSocial sciences. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aexternal financing, stock, insurance, property, casualty, auto, rate regulation, policies, tax law, taxation, industrial organization, mutuals, finance, economics, nonfiction, business, public policy, welfare, social systems, economy, risk, benefits, security, money, cost, growth, government, success, united states, accident, liability.1 aBohn, James G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorn, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradford, David F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradford, David F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGentry, William M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGron, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Brian J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJaffee, Dwight M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLogue, Kyle D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLucas, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRussell, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuponcic, Susan J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relator